I’ve been really looking forward to sharing this latest song with you all. To me it embodies the sound I’ve been working on since I started slow magic. Some songs come from an obvious place but some others seem to just happen out of thin air and when the song is done you just say “wow I don’t know how this happened but I’m glad it did” and this is one of those songs. I’ve been able to follow my creative impulses and direction more freely since becoming fully independent and working with a solid and supportive team and I’m so thankful for that. ❤️ anyway I’ll stop typing so you can go listen. :)

Love,

My new single ‘Avoiding Pain’ is out now! New album coming this summer ✨

What do we lose by avoiding our pain? I finished this song in the midst of learning that I had lost a family member. I spent a lot of time grieving and mourning for that person and reflecting on times in the past. There was a rush of nostalgic feelings and extreme pain that reminded me that we cannot go back to those times. Although I had been thinking about the meaning of the song and the vocal samples for a while, it became even clearer during my period of mourning. I hope people can find their own meaning and understanding in the words and music of this song and remember not to be afraid of their emotions, and to talk to others about them. ❤️

one way i personally avoid pain is by avoiding social media. lately i’ve been trying to get to a healthier place with my mental health and more and more i’m recognizing social media as a challenging place to be. the problem in the avoidance is that I don’t get the opportunity to connect with my friends and fans as much. I’m working on getting to a healthier place with social media though. maybe you also feel similarly? I am someone who often feels social anxiety and lately I’ve realized more that this can translate directly to social media anxiety as well. even sharing this personally makes me feel vulnerable but thats ok. ♡ let’s keep feeling together.

🪞here’s a glimpse into the last year of making Forgotten Feels 🪞 what’s your favorite song on it so far? :)

“Forgotten Feels is my fifth album, and it's a reflection of the past and a glimpse into the infinite future. Through this album, I explore themes of loss, conflicting emotions, escapism, nostalgia, and the feeling of freedom. Even after doing Slow Magic for over a decade, the process feels as exciting and fresh as the first few songs made in my small studio apartment. With total creative independence, I followed my heart and instinct on these songs, not guided by outside forces, label pressures, or trends. The album also includes collaborations with some amazing artist Laxcity, Juuku, Mariel Eve and Evalyn. These songs are still made in my bedroom, just in a different apartment.”

When I first started working on what eventually became “forgotten feels” I was trying to imagine what a follow up to my first album ▲ might sound like. Solitude came out of that exploration. I took the most definitive “slow magic” sounds I could think of, but tried to approach them in a new way. Over the years trying to maintain a unique but consistent sound and “brand” has been an interesting challenge that sometimes gets in the way of true creative expression. Lately I feel much more free to let the music happen naturally and follow my intuitions when sitting down to create. I’m sure a lot of you can relate to this creative struggle. I’m encouraging you to push through any self-critical thoughts or outside pressures and be true to U ♡
